<P><BR>Erm, that's the problem actually.&nbsp; It's defined by-mob.</P>
<P>Therefore, when they ran the batch process to flag raid mobs for all LDoN Raid spawnable mobs, some of the mobs in that table actually showed up in other non-raid locations.</P>
<P>In order to fix that, they'd have to locate which ones have multi-presence, and create a new mob for either the raid-spawned or the group-spawned so that they can be appropiately differentiated.</P>
				
